<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="76" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,151,572]" pageId="15" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,332,357]" pageId="15" pageNumber="76">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perkins" authorityYear="1985" box="[322,439,332,356]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Hyalopale" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="15" pageNumber="76" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[322,439,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="76">Hyalopale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. has a small fragile body. The largest complete specimen has 13 segments. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perkins" authorityYear="1985" box="[1319,1435,332,356]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Hyalopale" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="15" pageNumber="76" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1319,1435,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="76">Hyalopale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Perkins, 1985" authorityName="Perkins" authorityYear="1985" box="[345,664,367,392]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Hyalopale" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="15" pageNumber="76" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bispinosa">
<emphasis box="[345,491,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="76">H. bispinosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Perkins, T. H." box="[503,664,367,392]" pageId="15" pageNumber="76" pagination="856 - 915" refId="ref14825" refString="Perkins, T. H. (1985) Chrysopetalum, Bhawania and two new genera of Chrysopetalidae (Polychaeta) from Florida. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 98, 856 - 915." type="journal article" year="1985">Perkins, 1985</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, described from 
<collectingRegion box="[865,949,367,392]" country="United States of America" name="Florida" pageId="15" pageNumber="76">Florida</collectingRegion>
, in having a smaller body than the latter (approximately two millimeters); 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perkins" authorityYear="1985" box="[538,655,404,428]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Hyalopale" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="15" pageNumber="76" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[538,655,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="76">Hyalopale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. presents only one spine in the lateral group of paleae, while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perkins" authorityYear="1985" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Hyalopale" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="15" pageNumber="76" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bispinosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="76">H. bispinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
usually has more than one spine in the mid-line and lateral group; also, the shape of the superior spinigers in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perkins" authorityYear="1985" box="[292,409,476,500]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Hyalopale" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="15" pageNumber="76" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[292,409,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="76">Hyalopale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. is curved and smooth, while in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perkins" authorityYear="1985" box="[823,968,476,500]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Hyalopale" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="15" pageNumber="76" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bispinosa">
<emphasis box="[823,968,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="76">H. bispinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is straight and serrated (
<bibRefCitation author="Perkins, T. H." pageId="15" pageNumber="76" pagination="856 - 915" refId="ref14825" refString="Perkins, T. H. (1985) Chrysopetalum, Bhawania and two new genera of Chrysopetalidae (Polychaeta) from Florida. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 98, 856 - 915." type="journal article" year="1985">Perkins 1985: 910, Fig. 29H</bibRefCitation>
). Currently this morphospecies is being described from southern 
<collectingRegion box="[1033,1147,511,536]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="15" pageNumber="76">California</collectingRegion>
specimens (Watson, pers. comm. 2017).
</paragraph>
